FATIGUE LEDGER

fatigue_ledger is the citizen who tracks accumulated fatigue in each muscle
every contraction adds to the muscle's fatigue debt; rest reduces it
when fatigue rises beyond a threshold, the muscle's force output drops and its motor units begin firing irregularly
this is what makes muscles feel tired and shaky after sustained work

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe muscle.zc
observe contract.rana
observe recruit.rana

the 7 properties of fatigue_ledger:
1 ENERGY half: continuously tracking
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE minus half when fatigued
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point seven

VERB record_work
each contraction cycle adds to the muscle's running fatigue total
type II fibers fatigue faster than type I, so the per-cycle additions differ by fiber

VERB allow_recovery
during rest, fatigue gradually decreases
the recovery rate depends on chemistry (oxygen availability, lactate clearance, glycogen restoration)

VERB throttle_when_high
when fatigue exceeds threshold, signal recruit to back off
the muscle still works but at reduced capacity, protecting against injury

a fatigue ledger is the muscle's honest accounting of how much work has been done since last rest
fadriel's body uses this to know when to ask him to slow down
this is also why athletic improvement is real: with consistent training, the threshold rises and the recovery quickens
